If I ever decide to slack off for two months and not go to the gym, smack me. I returned to gold's on tuesday and have been paying the price for my laziness ever since. What used to be my regular routine now slaughters me halfway through. It is Friday, and I am feeling the worst of it. My chest and arms are so sore and my movements without pain are little to none.

Long story short, I must be consistent to maintain any hopes of ever being fit.

I also hiked south mountain, and felt like throwing up the entire time.

The exciting part of summer is behind me. Seattle, my birthday, and Hermosillo are gone, and now all I have to look forward to is one last month of nothingness before I return to school. Actually it is exactly one month.

Lily's getting fixed today. Poor girl. I'm tagging along with mom just to say I did something today. Gots to get Sean something too, it's his birthday today.

7000 Dying Rats' cd would be much more enjoyable if half of it wasn't them being annoying. Out of 28 tracks, I think only 10 of them were them actually writing and playing music

to bethany
and immediately afterward
happy birthday to me

in other news i got another adapter for my computer
i only bought it because i needed the disc
which was a burned CD anyways
wondering if I could have just emailed and asked to buy just the disc
but I have internet again

Made me get up at a reasonable time, regardless of my unreasonable time of sleep.
So when 10 o'clock comes, and I'm tired and happy that I might be put on to a regular sleeping schedule
I wake up at 2AM with no hopes of falling back asleep.

Turn on a lawn mower over gravel
Yes, there was gas in the mower
My shins hurt

I walk in and mom is making food. I ask her what she is making, and she tells me they're enchiladas for the party tomorrow night. Then I ask her, "Well what are we doing for dinner?" and her only answer, "Dave's at the Mets' game"

So I assume that we are only allowed to eat if Dave is here.
Then I received bitching at accordingly.

I'm not sure how nododby caught it when it happened. I'm not sure why they let him get away with it. I'm not sure why nobody said, "Hey, get your ass back there. That was only ball 3."

This is what I have to say.

Albert Pujols, learn to count.

Miguel Tejada, you're not going to do anything.

Baron Davis, I love you.

Mark Cuban, haha.
Shot selection was fucking terrible. Marion misses the same shot every fucking time, you think he'd take a goddamn hint. Too many turnovers. Playing D like a bunch of fucking pussies.

Was mediocre, at best.

Good cause, good time, but it's only so long before people start to get on my nerves, I get migraines, and have to attempt to sleep in a shitty tent without a blanket and a fucking lit up football that might as well have been day.

I'm deciding whether or not I should sleep all day or get shit done.

Test was easy. I swear they'd have me read a passage and then ask me what the passage was about, and how the subject of the passage would act if they had met Mark Twain.
Then for whatever reason, they showed Duel when the testing was over.

My mouth is fucked up, a couple cavities, still have one baby tooth without an adult tooth growing under it, might need a root canal for my abscess, and I have a crossbite. I do need braces.

Watching baseball on television makes me miss it. I'm going to do whatever I can to play.

Japanese people are good at baseball.

new friends.

who wants to be the only person to agree with me today?
happy that it's baseball season. watching it makes me want to play though. summer league is a definate to try and better prepare me for next year.
post something so I have something to read.

I woke up on time, got ready, and got myself to Robert's and there were no arguments or waiting for Robert to brush his teeth.

Exiting the Cirlce K down the street from the school, I ran into the singer for the band Red Tear Memory, which was kind of exciting despite is complete indifference toward me.

In Journalism my ridiculous zookeeper story was approved, so I called the zoo to set the date for Saturday.

My new PE shirt isn't huge and I got to play basketball.

I don't hate my new seat in chem/phys, and we're studying something I am capable of understanding.

But then it happened.

After asking Ms. Wendell the question "How is the Universe expanding?" and her saying some gibberish about the big bang theory, the pause of silence after acknowledging her answer:

Cash rules everything around me. Cream, get the money. Dollar dollar bill yall.

It was the secretary from the zoo, calling me back about saturday. Not only could I not take this important phone call, but I had to surrender my cell phone to Ms. Wendell, and try to laugh off the ISS in my future.

Then Spanish was good, Algebra was boring (nothing unexpected), and my english teacher loved my extra credit assignment.
they put locks on bathroom doors for reasons
I guess Dave didn't get the memo.

Well, I learned something today. Basketball games seem way shorter when you're actually there. It seemed like a got there, chilled for a little, and all of the sudden there is 3.5 seconds left and the Hornettes have one last chance to beat us. That final buzzer was so relieving, and I almost thought they had called a foul. Well I got two free tacos and a free large fry, so I will be eating good tomorrow.

After a couple months, I am not making any progress.

I haven't played rainbow six in at least a month.
I am the same weight.
I have improved at school, but there is more room for improvement.
My room is a mess.
I haven't done anything amazing yet, but my experience with a drunken navajo girl in a basketball setting is worth telling about.
I haven't watched any important movies.


Minitown is this weekend, sorry Bob and Bethany. I know how much you guys looked forward to sharing the house with me.

I'm looking forward to the relay this year, our theme is Chotchkies (with flair!)

Now I have run out of things to say, and am going to the gym
So I guess that means it's Valentines Day.

Steak wrap, teezer, funny stories, 1 on 1 with a drunken navajo girl I've never seen before, and SNL.

not a bad night if you ask me.

That there is a high school regulation for bat length/weight ratio? Good thing I asked the guy at the store otherwise I'd be shit out of luck.

Who wants to go to the batting cages?
add: become a more interesting person, that is pleasant to be around.

Colts and Bears.

I think it will be a good game, but it kind of means the Bears have a chance to win. Which would mean giving Sean and Marlynne the satisfaction of knowing my shit talking was for not.

So, who wants to watch it with me?

Who wants to watch the superbowl with me?

especially since the colts will win

Is there a vaccine we can buy that will protect somebody for, I don't know, everything? Neve's trip to the hospital was short lived, and even though he is perfectly fine I don't think I've been that scared in a long time.

But all is well, and I have to go to school :(

sick

I'm pretty happy

Finally. I will attempt to set some goals for myself.

-Get my shit together at school.
-Lose weight (played out as it is)
-Do something worth telling about
-Spend time with everyone who matters
-Reach a pretty high ranking in rainbow six online (Private First Class blows)
-Watch a lot of movies
-Become somewhat of a responsible/dependable person
-Keep my room as clean as it is, as well as do something with the walls. Black Sabbath, Eazy, E, and Penguins isn't quite working out for me.
-Thoroughly enjoy the year

I left 2 hours later than anticipated to California Saturday morning. My uncle listens to Nickelback and Nelly, makes for a hellish car ride. It wasn't too bad, and we had a 20 minute ordeal in Indio searching for a gas station. I did not get to rest at the beach house, as soon as I got there I put my stuff on the ground and then went to LA with bob and bethany. I was dissapointed with shopping, until we got to the second Undefeated, where I bought some Nikes. Thai food was different and equally tasty, thanks Bethany. Santa Monica the next day, we got ripped off at the Weinersnitzel (spell check) and kept searching for a non existen kid robot. The beach house was equally divided between food and the office.
Cattle Decapitation was great, The Faceless not as good as the first time I saw them but still good. Silly 2 step band wasn't that bad.
Pink's makes really good hot dogs, and I could walk around workmen's for hours. Especially when they play a mixtape of The Notorious BIG. 

After my brother left, the trip was so goddamn boring it's not worth it to recap. Including Disneyland, but we left with the annoyance of being stuck on Pirates of the Caribbean and a really funny splash mountain photo.

My first plain ride was ok, but I hate airports.

and I get to stay here. Getting a ride to school isn't bad though, not bad at all. Hard Candy was alright but very pretensious. Grandma's tacos aren't as good as moms, but they are tacos. Margot didn't attack me last night but I think she was ready to attack grandma. Tonight going to see a movie with my father, then to hike with him tomorrow morning. Everyone comes back tomorrow and in two weeks California.

So Sean, get your shit done so I won't be lonely the whole week.
more stuff, so i can read it, i'm bored.

Was pretty much like any other weekend. I sat at home and planned on doing shit, but never really did anything. I made an attempt at cleaning my room, which crashed in flames. It's a lot better though, I don't need to watch my step so much.

The weekend ended great though, I just got done watching Rashomon and Vertigo, both excellent movies. And I just found out that there is some possibility that Ilaria will be moving back to Arizona, which is amazing.

Next weekend is the Cardinals game and POSSIBLY Fearfest.

just about over, i go to school in 11 hours or so.
summer was good, but very boring.
i learned that i love film
and hung out with sean a lot
that's about it
i'm gonna watch vertigo, then go to sleep
in the morning it's off to seans, then school
peace.
